					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">ZomCoder wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">When FCEUXD hits a breakpoint, I presume everything gets "frozen" that is, vblank will quit firing?</div><br />Yes. The debugger essentially freezes the master clock, which gets divided down into the PPU clock and the CPU clock.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">but obviously this won't be sufficient in all cases.  Also there's the problem of identifying where the breakpoints should be; however I think if I just .db'd a string before each big routine I should be able to find it in the debugger..</div>
<br />At least one of the FCEU variants has the ability to import a symbol table. Every 6502 assembler that I've seen can write a symbol table in some text format, and a quick script in Perl or Python might be able to translate the symbol table into the format that FCEU expects.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

